This paper deals with data privacy problems in the context of databases, which is a core topic in computer science databases (cs.DB). The paper also involves complexity analysis and NP-hardness proofs, which are common in the sub-categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses graph partitioning problems, which are relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves information theory concepts such as entropy, which is a topic in the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT).
